 :tx/rationale "C9-4 IMPLEMENTATION DETAIL: Contradiction detection across observations using per-agent grouping within concept clusters. WHERE: crates/braid-kernel/src/signal.rs, after detect_logical() around line 480. NEW TYPE: ObservationContradiction struct with fields: concept (EntityId), concept_name (String), position_a (String — agent A claim excerpt), position_b (String — agent B claim excerpt), agent_a (AgentId), agent_b (AgentId), disagreement_type (String — severity or soundness or recommendation). NEW FUNCTION: detect_observation_contradictions(store: &Store) -> Vec<ObservationContradiction>. ALGORITHM: (1) Call crate::concept::corroboration_analysis(store) to get per-concept agent groupings. (2) For each concept with 2+ distinct agents: group member observation bodies by agent. (3) Simple keyword contradiction detection across agent groups: SEVERITY — one agent body contains 'Critical' while another contains 'Low' or 'Medium' within 20 chars of 'Severity'. SOUNDNESS — one contains 'SOUND' while another contains 'UNSOUND' (case-sensitive to avoid false matches on 'unsound reasoning'). (4) For each detected contradiction, extract 100-char excerpts around the contradicting keywords as position_a and position_b. (5) Return sorted by concept member_count descending (contradictions in larger clusters are more important). KEY REUSE: Builds on detect_aleatory() pattern in signal.rs which already groups by agent. The difference: detect_aleatory works on (entity, attribute) assertions; this works on observation body text within concept clusters. TESTS: (A) test_contradiction_severity_mismatch — agent A says Critical, agent B says Low, detected. (B) test_no_false_positive_agreement — both agents say Critical, no contradiction. (C) test_contradiction_soundness — agent A says SOUND, agent B says UNSOUND-RECOVERABLE, detected. EFFORT: 2h. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/signal.rs. DEPENDS-ON: C9-1 (t-6090a2ed) for per-agent grouping. TRACES TO: INV-SIGNAL-001, INV-DELIBERATION-001."
